  "texts": [
    "As an alternative to traditional diagnostic methods, facial expression analysis has shown promise in early detection of ASD, as children with ASD often exhibit distinctive patterns that differentiate them from typically developing children.",
    "Assistive technology has proven to be an effective tool in improving the quality of life for individuals with ASD.",
    "In this study, we developed a real-time emotion identification system for autistic children to detect their emotions in case of pain or anger.",
    "The emotion recognition system consists of three stages: face identification, facial feature extraction, and feature categorization.",
    "The proposed system can detect six facial emotions: anger, fear, joy, natural, sadness, and surprise."
  ],
